    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "41. Transmission Support"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "42. Stiffener removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582200_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "43. Torque converter disconnection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582201_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the torque converter cover (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "44. Transmission Assy. removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582202_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the transmission case mounting bolts on the front side of the transmission."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582203_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Remove the transmission case mounting bolts on the rear side of the transmission."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Be careful not to drop the torque converter."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "45. Torque converter removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582204_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the torque converter (A) and knock pin (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Be careful not to connect wires and tubes incorrectly. Also, be sure that cords and tubes do not become entangled or come into contact with other parts."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Torque Converter Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582205_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install a new O-ring (B) on the torque converter (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Transmission Assy. installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582206_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Support the transmission with the transmission jack and install it in the cylinder block."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582207_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Install the transmission case mounting bolts on the front side of the transmission."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Torque Converter Connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582208_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn the crankshaft pulley to install the drive plate mounting bolts (A) (6 pcs.) and connect the drive plate to the torque converter."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Stiffener Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582209_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Tighten the stiffener (A) tightly to the cylinder block, transmission and oil pan, and temporarily tighten."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Left Side Drive Shaft Inboard Joint Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582210_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install a new set ring (B) on the inboard joint (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The drive shaft must be inserted horizontally to prevent damage to the differential oil seal.",
        "Install carefully to prevent dust and other debris from entering the transmission."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Right Side Drive Shaft Inboard Joint Installation (2WD models)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582211_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install a new set ring (B) on the inboard joint (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The drive shaft must be inserted horizontally to prevent damage to the differential oil seal.",
        "Install carefully to prevent dust and other debris from entering the transmission."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Transfer Breather Tube Assy. installation (4WD models)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582212_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Subframe Connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582213_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Lift the sub-frame (A) up to the body by supporting it with the transmission jack (B) using a square timber, etc. Temporarily install the new subframe mounting bolts (C). Temporarily attach the underload path mounting bolts (D)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Subframe Tightening",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000865",
          "label": "Subframe Tightening",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Anda Load Path Rod Tightening",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000864",
          "label": "Anda Load Path Rod Tightening",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Torque Rod Temporary tightening"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582214_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Lay a plate on the transmission and support it with a transmission jack. Install the torque rod and tighten the new mounting nut (A). When installing the bolt on the front sub-frame side, align the non-turn plate (B) of the bolt with the notch (C) in the guide section of the front sub-frame, insert the bolt and install the nut. Temporarily tighten the new mounting bolts (D). Remove the transmission jack."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "12. Lower ball joint Connection",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000665",
          "label": "Lower ball joint Connection",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "13. Stabilizer link connection (for vehicles equipped with stabilizer)",
      "refs": [
