      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582221_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Install the harness bracket (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Ensure that there is no rust, debris, oil, etc. in the coupler."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "25. Transmission-side control wire installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "544_5.0_jpn_11582222_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Apply a thin coat of molybdenum grease to the inside of the control wire end bushing (A). Install the control wire bracket (B). Attach the control wire end with the bushing facing up to the control lever (C) and insert the control pin (D) to secure it in place. Attach the snap pin (F) to the control pin. Install the snap pin (F) onto the control pin securely until the tip of the snap pin (G) comes out of the bottom of the guide (H) on the control lever."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Push the control pin into the hole (E) of the control lever until it hits the hole (B) and install it securely."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The hook (I) of the snap pin should rest on the chamfer (J) of the control pin hole."
      ]
    },
    {
